<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1830" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1830">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 816.001Q4/1.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Minister of
                                    Salvador</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-03">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 3, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 23rd ultimo, with which you enclose an
                            autograph letter from Dr. Alfonso Quiñonez M., announcing to the
                            President his assumption of the Chief Magistracy of the Republic of
                            Salvador, by reason of the leave of absence granted to Señor Don Carlos
                            Melendez by the National Assembly.</p>
                        <p>I have taken pleasure in forwarding the letter to the President, whose
                            reply will be delivered through the American Minister at San
                            Salvador.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>